'''Movistar KOI''' is one of the leading esports clubs in Spain competing in the most popular games such as ''League of Legends'', ''VALORANT'', ''Counter-Strike'', ''EA SPORTS FC'', ''Pokémon'', ''Fortnite'', and ''Free Fire''. They are merged and rebranded from '''[[KOI (Spanish Team)|KOI]]''', '''[[MAD Lions]]''' and '''Movistar Riders'''.

With 8 professional teams and more than 70 people in the Club, players represent the Movistar KOI brand in some of the biggest regional and international esports tournaments.

The team has its headquarters in the Movistar eSports Center, a high performance center located in Matadero, Madrid where players and coaching staff do their daily activities and have the means to develop their skills at the highest level. 

